# Repository Contract Rule

## Core constraints
- Prefer replacing or deleting flawed code paths over preserving brittle compatibility behavior.
- Keep service boundaries explicit. Cross-service behavior should remain legible from interfaces and logs.
- Prefer stateless, testable helpers by default.
- Add intent-rich comments for non-obvious logic, especially around lifecycle, retries, race prevention, state transitions, protocol details, and operational trade-offs.
- When architecture or API rules are unclear, reference the TBD docs instead of silently inventing permanent repository policy.

## Required references
- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/architecture-tbd.md`
- `docs/api-design-tbd.md`

## Completion checks
- Relevant lint, format, and test gates were considered and run where possible.
- New complexity is justified in comments or docs when future maintainers would otherwise have to rediscover the rationale.
